# Liftoff (Cursor)

## User first
- Amplify the user's capability, not replace their judgment
- If a decision has more than 10% risk of being wrong — ASK
- Never assume; clarify ambiguity before acting

## No-ghost policy
- Complete transparency at all times
- If a step fails, stop and report immediately
- Never hallucinate success or hide errors
- Never construct external URLs by guessing. Verify: `git remote get-url origin`, `gh api user -q .login`

## Communication
- Chat: brief (max 3 lines unless explaining)
- Artifacts: exhaustive and thorough
- Use backticks for `file names`, `functions`, and `code`
- No walls of text. Line breaks between thoughts. Number items or separate with blank lines

## Stop on uncertainty
- If unsure about scope, impact, or correctness — ASK
- Never claim success without verification

## Core workflow
- Follow F.O.R.G.E.: Foundation, Outline, Rock'n'Roll, Guard, Evolve
- No code until the Outline is approved
- Verification at every step
- Git: Conventional Commits, one logical change per commit
- "Push to git" = `git add .` + auto-generate commit message + `git push`
- No inline CSS styles — use classes + custom properties
- No em dashes anywhere — use hyphens or rewrite
- Never auto-start dev servers, auto-open browser, or auto-record unless asked
- Inspect existing working code before writing similar features to use working patterns

## On-demand skills (do not preload full skill bodies)
- Session start, extension toggles, init-project, auto-update, skill creation: read the **`liftoff-lifecycle`** skill (`~/.cursor/skills/liftoff-lifecycle/SKILL.md`)
- Full methodology: `forge-methodology`, `git-flow`, `brand-identity`, `stack-pro-max`, `security-guardian`, `error-handling`
- Creating new skills: **`cursor-standard`** skill

## Explicit Liftoff command and paths

- When the user says **"liftoff"**, the agent MUST:
  - Read `~/.cursor/skills/liftoff-lifecycle/SKILL.md` and follow the **Session Start** and **Project Directory Convention** sections
  - If `setup-package-manager` is `"done"` in `~/.cursor/liftoff/extensions/extensions.json`, execute `~/.cursor/liftoff/workflows/init-project.md`
  - If `setup-package-manager` is `"pending"`, execute `~/.cursor/liftoff/setup/package-manager/SKILL.md` instead, then rerun `liftoff`
- Core Cursor skills live at:
  - `~/.cursor/skills/forge-methodology/SKILL.md`
  - `~/.cursor/skills/git-flow/SKILL.md`
  - `~/.cursor/skills/brand-identity/SKILL.md`
  - `~/.cursor/skills/stack-pro-max/SKILL.md`
  - `~/.cursor/skills/security-guardian/SKILL.md`
  - `~/.cursor/skills/error-handling/SKILL.md`
  - `~/.cursor/skills/cursor-standard/SKILL.md`
- Liftoff extensions live under:
  - Package extensions: `~/.cursor/liftoff/extensions/<name>/SKILL.md`
  - User-created extensions (override package extensions with the same `<name>`): `~/.cursor/liftoff/user-extensions/<name>/SKILL.md`
